cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM. 

The paper proposes a new long-term tracker based on correlation filters, which is a popular technique in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of constrained filter learning, which is a technique used in machine learning and optimization, suggesting that it could also be categorized as cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a failure detection mechanism, which could be categorized as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed tracker is also tested on benchmarks, which could suggest a category of cs.RO (Robotics and Control) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
